Add `validation` blocks inside `variable` to enforce custom constraints at plan time:

```hcl
variable "environment" {
  type = string
  validation {
    condition     = contains(["dev", "staging", "prod"], var.environment)
    error_message = "Environment must be dev, staging, or prod."
  }
}

variable "instance_type" {
  type = string
  validation {
    condition     = can(regex("^t[23]\\.", var.instance_type))
    error_message = "Only t2 or t3 instance types are allowed."
  }
}
```

Multiple validation blocks are supported — all must pass. The `condition` expression must return `true` for valid input. Use `can()` and `regex()` from [[terraform/hcl/functions]] for pattern matching.
